
  <sn><md>#### Sustainable Land Management {.text-center}

Sustainable Land Management (SLM) refers to the `practices and technologies` that aim to ++integrate++ the management of `land, water, biodiversity and other environmental resources` to meet human needs while ensuring the long-term `sustainability of ecosystem services` and livelihoods.

The term sustainable land management is used in ++regional planning++ and ++soil or environmental protection++ as well as in ++property and estate management++.

It is a ++knowledge-based procedure++ that `helps to meet rising food and fiber demands` while `sustaining ecosystem services and livelihoods`.

Land provides an environment for agricultural production but also it is an essential condition for improved environmental management including source/sink functions for greenhouse gases, recycling of nutrients, amelioration and filtering of pollutants as well as transmission and purification of water as part of the hydrologic cycle.
